Non-routine and discretionary purchases, include but are not limited to, goods or services that are:
1. Non-recurring or one-time purchases;
2. Unusual purchases;
3. Pilot programs;
4. District level awards and honors in excess of $2,500;
5. Purchases that materially differ in type, scope, purpose, or cost from prior purchases;
6. Purchases that do not align with Board Policy EMB (Local), EFA (Local), or EFB (Local); or
7. Purchases for professional services, consulting services, technology systems or software platforms, and large equipment or infrastructure items.
